There are lots of options for names -- not really sure on a convention for _all_ decorators yet -- or even if it matters -- maybe it depends on what the decorator does.

example:

```js
import React, { Component } from 'react';
import wrapStateHelpers from 'react-state-helpers';

@wrapStateHelpers
export default class MyComponent extends Component { ... }
```

Not sure of the recommended default export name should be an action, a noun, or an -able suffix. 

